  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Send 300 Kids to School for USD300/Child in the PH</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Did you know that while public school is free in the Philippines, some students, especially the poor, still find it hard to attend classes? Due to financial constraints, poor students encounter problems to sustain daily expenses of transportation and food, and financing their uniform, school supplies, and school projects. At USD300 per student in Senior High, the project aims to help 300 poor kids cover these expenses for a school year to facilitate attendance and good performance in school.</narrative>
  </description>
